  </object>
  <br/>
 </font>
 <font face="Arial">
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
 </font>
 <p>
  <br/>
  <font face="Arial">
   When discussing “countable items” you should use “
   <a href="many.htm">
    MANY
   </a>
   ,” 
  “
   <a href="../h/how-many.htm">
    how-MANY
   </a>
   ,” or the one-handed version of “
   <a href="../h/how-much.htm">
    how-MUCH
   </a>
   ?” (Which is often 
  interpreted as “how much” – as in “What is the cost of that?”).
  </font>
  <br/>
 </p>
 <p>
  <font face="Arial">
   "How much?"-(countable)
   <br/>
   <br/>
   Sample sentence:
   <br/>
   WAITRESS, HOW-MUCH SHOULD T-I-P? (How much should you tip a 
			waitress?)
   <br/>
  </font>
 </p>
 <p>
  <object classid="CLSID:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=8,0,0,0" height="275" id="FVS0" width="320">
